question_text:
What is the measure of the missing angle?
_°
solution: The sum of the four angles must be 360°. The three angles you know measure 78°, 142°, and 67°.

Write an equation and find the measure of the unknown angle.
78° + 142° + 67° + ? = 360°
287° + ? = 360°
? = 360° - 287°
? = 73°
The measure of the missing angle is 73°.
